id L. Lawrence Convention Center|Lawrence Convention Center]], [[Pittsburgh]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|14\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} Anthony Green\n|TKO\n|8 {{small|(10)}}\n|{{small|17/09/1999}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Flickenger Athletic Center, [[Buffalo, New York]]}}\n|align=left|{{small|Won USA New York State Heavyweight title.}}\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|13\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Jamaica}} Rowyan Wallace\n|KO\n|2 {{small|(6)}}\n|{{small|04/06/1999}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[The Blue Horizon|Blue Horizon]], [[Philadelphia]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|12\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} Brian Sargent\n|KO\n|1 {{small|(6)}}\n|{{small|24/04/1999}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Portland Art Museum|Arts Museum]], [[Portland, Oregon]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|11\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} Dwayne Hall\n|TKO\n|1 {{small|(4)}}\n|{{small|19/02/1999}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Turning Stone Resort & Casino|Turning Stone Casino]], [[Verona, New York]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|10\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} Rodney McSwain\n|TKO\n|3 {{small|(6)}}\n|{{small|03/12/1998}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|Sheraton Hotel, [[Houston]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|9\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} Jihad Abdulaziz\n|UD\n|4\n|{{small|09/10/1998}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Capitol Theater (Port Chester, New York)|Capitol Theatre]], [[Port Chester, New York]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|8\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|Mexico}} Martin Lopez\n|KO\n|3 {{small|(6)}}\n|{{small|27/08/1998}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Arena Theatre]], [[Houston]]}}\n|align=left|\n|- align=center\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|7\u20130\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Kevin Rosier]]\n|TKO\n|2 {{small|(4)}}\n|{{small|26/07/1998}}\n|align=left|{{flagicon|USA}}